		.gs-guide-section
			.container-sm
				.gs-guide__header
					h2.gs-guide__title
						span.gs-guide__title-count 2
						.gs-guide__title-label Commands
				h3 Install the CMS and app generators
				p You'll be using the <a href='https://github.com/RiversideLabs/generator-landmark', target='_blank'>LandmarkJS generator</a> and <a href='https://github.com/RiversideLabs/generator-landmark-connect', target='_blank'>Landmark Connect generator</a> made with <a href='http://yeoman.io/', target='_blank'>Yeoman</a>. In your root directory run:
				pre.command-line
					| npm install -g generator-landmark
					| 
					| npm install -g generator-landmark-connect
				.alert.alert-danger NOTE: The app generator is not yet available.
				
				h3 Create a folder for your project
				p Create your project wherever you want:
				pre.command-line mkdir my-test-project
				
				p Then make sure you're in your new project:
				pre.command-line cd my-test-project
			
				h3 Create subfolders for LandmarkJS and Landmark Connect
				pre.command-line
					| mkdir my-project-cms
					| mkdir my-project-app
				.alert.alert-danger NOTE: The app generator is not yet available.
				
				h3 Run the generators
				
				p Make sure you are in the CMS subfolder, then run the CMS generator:
				pre.command-line
					| cd my-project-cms
					| yo landmark
				
				p Make sure you are in the app subfolder, then run the app generator:
				pre.command-line
					| cd my-project-app
					| yo landmark-connect
				.alert.alert-danger NOTE: The app generator is not yet available.
				
				p Both generators will ask you a few questions about what features you'd like to include, then configure and copy all the files you'll need into your project.
				p It will also install dependencies from npm so you're ready to go.
		
